  "texts": [
    "However, GPT-3.5 struggles with the direction and nature of causation, hence we recommend limiting these maps to associations (i.e., undirected graphs).",
    "We also note that fine-tuning the iteration parameter can create maps whose structure partially resembles human-made maps, as it is possible to match some aspects (e.g., number of nodes or density) but not all.",
    "Our inspection of errors revealed that GPT-3.5 did not have notable issues of hallucination and excelled at finding synonyms/antonyms, but the lack of understanding regarding the sequence of events produced erroneous and occasionally controversial causal connections.",
    "Our system could thus serve to compare complex systems depicted in white papers by turning them into undirected graphs and leveraging the abundant literature on graph comparison.",
    "There are two interesting avenues for future research."
